For the new versions of the Kali 

You will need to create an venv for install the tool- No tools or python scripts directly get install in the global pip system so to prevent we create an venv environment for it. 

# 1️⃣ Install venv tools if missing
navigate to the place where you are installing the tool or have git cloned the tool. 

# 2️⃣ Create a local virtual environment inside dirsearch
python3 -m venv .venv

# 3️⃣ Activate it
source .venv/bin/activate

# 4️⃣ Upgrade pip inside the venv
pip install --upgrade pip 

# 5️⃣ Install all requirements safely
pip install -r requirements.txt
